{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GLContextProtocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gdk\/documentation\/Gdk\/DrawContextProtocol","preciseIdentifier":"s:3Gdk19DrawContextProtocolP","text":"DrawContextProtocol"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GdkGLContext"},{"type":"text","text":"s are created for a surface using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.Surface.create_gl_context"},{"type":"text","text":"], and the context will match"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the characteristics of the surface."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GdkGLContext"},{"type":"text","text":" is not tied to any particular normal framebuffer."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For instance, it cannot draw to the surface back buffer. The GDK"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"repaint system is in full control of the painting to that. Instead,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you can create render buffers or textures and use [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cairo_draw_from_gl"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in the draw function of your widget to draw them. Then GDK will handle"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the integration of your rendering with that of other widgets."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Support for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GdkGLContext"},{"type":"text","text":" is platform-specific and context creation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can fail, returning "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" context."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GdkGLContext"},{"type":"text","text":" has to be made “current” in order to start using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it, otherwise any OpenGL call will be ignored."}]},{"anchor":"Creating-a-new-OpenGL-context","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Creating a new OpenGL context"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In order to create a new "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GdkGLContext"},{"type":"text","text":" instance you need a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GdkSurface"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which you typically get during the realize call of a widget."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GdkGLContext"},{"type":"text","text":" is not realized until either [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.GLContext.make_current"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.GLContext.realize"},{"type":"text","text":"] is called. It is possible to specify"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"details of the GL context like the OpenGL version to be used, or whether"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the GL context should have extra state validation enabled after calling"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.Surface.create_gl_context"},{"type":"text","text":"] by calling [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.GLContext.realize"},{"type":"text","text":"]."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If the realization fails you have the option to change the settings of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GdkGLContext"},{"type":"text","text":" and try again."}]},{"anchor":"Using-a-GdkGLContext","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Using a GdkGLContext"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You will need to make the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GdkGLContext"},{"type":"text","text":" the current context before issuing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"OpenGL calls; the system sends OpenGL commands to whichever context is current."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It is possible to have multiple contexts, so you always need to ensure that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the one which you want to draw with is the current one before issuing commands:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"c","code":["gdk_gl_context_make_current (context);"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can now perform your drawing using OpenGL commands."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can check which "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GdkGLContext"},{"type":"text","text":" is the current one by using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.GLContext.get_current"},{"type":"text","text":"]; you can also unset any "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GdkGLContext"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that is currently set by calling [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.GLContext.clear_current"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLContextProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GdkGLContext"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLContext"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLContextRef"},{"type":"text","text":" as a lighweight, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gdk\/glcontextprotocol"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gdk\/documentation\/Gdk\/DrawContextProtocol","doc:\/\/Gdk\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/Gdk\/10GLibObject0B8ProtocolP"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gdk\/documentation\/Gdk\/GLContext","doc:\/\/Gdk\/documentation\/Gdk\/GLContextRef"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforming Types","type":"conformingTypes"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gdk\/documentation\/Gdk\/GLContextProtocol","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GdkGLContext"},{"type":"text","text":" is an object representing a platform-specific"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"OpenGL draw context."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GLContextProtocol"}],"title":"GLContextProtocol","roleHeading":"Protocol","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"protocol","externalID":"s:3Gdk17GLContextProtocolP","modules":[{"name":"Gdk"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GLContextProtocol"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Gdk\/documentation\/Gdk"]]},"topicSections":[{"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gdk\/documentation\/Gdk\/GLContextProtocol\/allowedApis","doc:\/\/Gdk\/documentation\/Gdk\/GLContextProtocol\/api","doc:\/\/Gdk\/documentation\/Gdk\/GLContextProt